# Manual HTTP calls for the Candidature API — these hit the RUNNING app (dev database).
# Run each request with the green ▶ in PhpStorm. Pick the "dev" environment (top-right).
# For automated, repeatable checks against the isolated test DB, see tests/Feature/Candidature.

### Register a valid candidature (expect 201 Created)
POST {{baseUrl}}/candidatures
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "full_name": "Ada Lovelace",
  "email": "ada@example.com",
  "years_of_experience": 7,
  "cv": "Mathematician and first programmer."
}

### Register the same email again (expect 409 Conflict)
POST {{baseUrl}}/candidatures
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "full_name": "Ada Again",
  "email": "ada@example.com",
  "years_of_experience": 3,
  "cv": "Duplicate."
}

### Same email in UPPERCASE (expect 409 Conflict — uniqueness is case-insensitive)
POST {{baseUrl}}/candidatures
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "full_name": "Ada Upper",
  "email": "ADA@EXAMPLE.COM",
  "years_of_experience": 3,
  "cv": "Duplicate."
}

### Malformed email (expect 422 Unprocessable Entity)
POST {{baseUrl}}/candidatures
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "full_name": "Bad Email",
  "email": "not-an-email",
  "years_of_experience": 2,
  "cv": "..."
}

### Negative years of experience (expect 422 Unprocessable Entity)
POST {{baseUrl}}/candidatures
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "full_name": "Negative Years",
  "email": "neg@example.com",
  "years_of_experience": -1,
  "cv": "..."
}

### Missing required field: no email (expect 422 Unprocessable Entity)
POST {{baseUrl}}/candidatures
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "full_name": "No Email",
  "years_of_experience": 4,
  "cv": "..."
}
